PARTE 14: HERENCIA DE MODELOS
================================================================

_inherit - Extender modelo base
- Herencia simple, comparte misma tabla
- Extiende funcionalidad sin modificar original

Ejemplo:
  # Modelo original (en módulo sale)
  class SaleOrder(models.Model):
      _name = 'sale.order'
      name = fields.Char()

  # Extender (en módulo custom)
  class SaleOrderExtended(models.Model):
      _name = 'sale.order'
      _inherit = 'sale.order'
      
      custom_field = fields.Char()
      
      def write(self, vals):
          result = super().write(vals)
          if 'state' in vals:
              self._custom_action()
          return result

_inherits - Herencia de delegación
- Crea Many2one con modelo padre
- Hereda campos pero en tabla separada

Ejemplo:
  class Partner(models.Model):
      _name = 'res.partner'
      name = fields.Char()

  class Customer(models.Model):
      _name = 'res.customer'
      _inherits = {'res.partner': 'partner_id'}
      
      partner_id = fields.Many2one(
          'res.partner',
          required=True
      )
      customer_code = fields.Char()

Acceso a campos:
  customer.name → accede a partner_id.name automáticamente

================================================================
PARTE 15: TRACKING Y AUDITORÍA
================================================================

tracking=True - Registrar cambios automáticamente
- Monitorea cambios en campos
- Aparece en timeline/Chatter
- Accesible vía mail.tracking.value

Ejemplo:
  class ClaimForm(models.Model):
      _name = 'claim.form'
      
      name = fields.Char(tracking=True)
      state = fields.Selection(
          [('new', 'Nuevo'), ('done', 'Resuelto')],
          tracking=True
      )
      internal_notes = fields.Text(tracking=False)

Ver cambios en código:
  changes = self.env['mail.tracking.value'].search([
      ('res_id', '=', record.id),
      ('res_model', '=', 'claim.form')
  ])

Invalidar caché:
  def custom_action(self):
      self.write({'name': 'New Value'})
      self.invalidate_cache()
      
      # O campos específicos
      self.invalidate_cache(['computed_field'])

================================================================
PARTE 16: EJEMPLO COMPLETO INTEGRADOR
================================================================

Ejemplo de modelo con varios decoradores:

  from odoo import models, fields, api
  from odoo.exceptions import ValidationError, UserError

  class ClaimForm(models.Model):
      _name = 'claim.form'
      _description = 'Formulario de Reclamación'

      name = fields.Char(
          required=True,
          tracking=True
      )
      claim_date = fields.Date(
          default='_default_claim_date',
          tracking=True
      )
      consumer_type = fields.Selection(
          [('person', 'Persona'), ('company', 'Empresa')],
          default='person'
      )
      amount = fields.Float()
      state = fields.Selection(
          [('new', 'Nuevo'), ('done', 'Resuelto')],
          default='new',
          tracking=True
      )
      total_days = fields.Integer(
          compute='_compute_total_days'
      )

      _sql_constraints = [
          ('check_amount',
           'CHECK (amount > 0)',
           'El monto debe ser positivo'),
      ]

      def _default_claim_date(self):
          return fields.Date.today()

      @api.depends('claim_date')
      def _compute_total_days(self):
          for record in self:
              if record.claim_date:
                  delta = fields.Date.today() - record.claim_date
                  record.total_days = delta.days
              else:
                  record.total_days = 0

      @api.constrains('amount')
      def _check_amount_range(self):
          for record in self:
              if record.amount > 10000:
                  raise ValidationError(
                      "El monto no puede ser mayor a 10000"
                  )

      @api.onchange('consumer_type')
      def _onchange_consumer_type(self):
          if self.consumer_type != 'company':
              self.company_name = False

      @api.ondelete(at_unlink=True)
      def _protect_resolved_claims(self):
          if self.state == 'done':
              raise UserError(
                  "No se puede eliminar una reclamación resuelta"
              )

      def action_resolve(self):
          self.state = 'done'

================================================================
DECORADORES DEPRECADOS (NO USAR)
================================================================

@api.multi (Odoo 13+) - DEPRECADO
  Indicaba que trabajaba con múltiples registros
  Ahora todos los métodos son multi por defecto

@api.one (Odoo 13+) - DEPRECADO
  Indicaba que trabajaba con un solo registro
  Ahora se usa bucle for en todos

Código viejo (NO USAR):
  @api.multi
  @api.one
  def get_total(self):
      return self.amount + self.tax

Código correcto:
  def get_total(self):
      for record in self:
          return record.amount + record.tax

